		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.ektoplazm.com/blog/ongoing-web-server-issues-an-update/comment-page-1#comment-32814">
			November 3, 2011 at 8:56 am</a>		</div>

		<p>Hi! Thanks for keeping it up for so long. Most others would have given up -and many have- long ago. Very nice and interesting view from the machine room, highly appreciated. Just one thought about mirroring: I wondered for quite some time why you haven&#8217;t ever considered mirroring your stuff at archive.org. Almost all netlabels do, many fully rely on archive.org for music files and only announce their releases locally, optionally with embedded preview players exported from there.<br />
I totally understand that you want to keep control over content in your own hands as well as keeping your stats accurate, but some fallback option could take a lot of heat from you when things don&#8217;t play nicely while keeping your users satisfied.<br />
just my 2 eurocents :)<br />
Tom (not associate with archive.org &#8211; they&#8217;re non-profit anyway, AFAIK)</p>

		<div class="reply">
